'''Moses Rischin''' (born 1925) is an American [[Jewish]] [[historian]], [[author]], [[lecturer]], [[editing|editor]], and [[emeritus professor]] of history at [[San Francisco State University]].<ref name="MJL">[http://www.myjewishlearning.com/history_community/About_Jewish_History_Community/MemoryTO/LowerEastSide.htm My Jewish Learning: The Lower East Side<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080111040059/http://www.myjewishlearning.com/history_community/About_Jewish_History_Community/MemoryTO/LowerEastSide.htm |date=2008-01-11 }}</ref><ref name="Lehrhaus">[http://www.lehrhaus.org/about/staff.html Lehrhaus Judaica - The Adult School For Jewish Studies<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080514200126/http://www.lehrhaus.org/about/staff.html |date=2008-05-14 }}</ref> He coined the phrase [[new Mormon history]] in a 1969 article of the same name.<ref name="Sunstone">http://www.sunstoneonline.com/magazine/issues/123/123-28-32.pdf{{dead link|date=February 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> Rischin is from [[New York City]].{{Citation needed|date=February 2008}} His undergraduate studies were at [[Brooklyn College]].<ref>[http://www.sfsu.edu/~bulletin/noindex/9496/faculty/fac-rs.htm Bulletin-Faculty R & S<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> [[Harvard University]] awarded him a [[PhD]] in 1957.<ref name="SFSU">{{cite web |url=http://bss.sfsu.edu/history/Advising%20Materials/Program%20Booklets/Booklet-graduate.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2008-02-21 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070709213846/http://bss.sfsu.edu/history/Advising%20Materials/Program%20Booklets/Booklet-graduate.pdf |archivedate=2007-07-09 |df= }}</ref> In addition to his professorship, he sits on the board for the ''Journal of American Ethnic History'' and on the council of the [[American Jewish History Society]].<ref name="Chadwyck">[http://iibp.chadwyck.com/infopage/publ/jae.htm Browse Journals<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref name="AJHS">[http://www.ajhs.org/academic/faculty_member.cfm?id=75 AJHS: Academic Council Member<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> There is an annual lecture given in his honor at the [[Western Jewish History Center]], where he is director.<ref name="Emanueldec05">[http://www.emanuelsf.org/downloads/chronicle/chron_dec05.pdf eelchron_dec05_final.indd<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070710004656/http://emanuelsf.org/downloads/chronicle/chron_dec05.pdf |date=2007-07-10 }}</ref><ref>[http://www.jewishsf.com/content/2-0-/module/displaystory/story_id/5309/edition_id/98/format/html/displaystory.html j. - Jewish history center marks three decades of capturing the past<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> There is a collection of historical essays published in Rischin's honor,<ref>''An Inventory of Promises: Essays on American Jewish History : In Honor of Moses Rischin'' by Jeffrey S. Gurock and Marc Lee Raphael (Carlson Publishing, 1996)</ref> and a supporting character, Meyer Meyer in the [[87th Precinct]] series, may have been partly modeled after him.<ref>[http://www.english.upenn.edu/~traister/mem.html Daniel Traister's Home Page-MEMORY<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>
Rischin is considered an authority on [[History of immigration to the United States|American ethnic and immigration history]]<ref>[http://www.essex.ac.uk/ecpr/events/jointsessions/paperarchive/uppsala/ws20/manor.pdf "Utopia as a camouflage : The case of Abe Cahan and his legacy<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref name="NYT06071993">{{cite news| url=https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9F0CE4DD123BF934A35755C0A965958260 | work=The New York Times | title=Abigail Rischin, David A. Moss | date=1993-06-07 | accessdate=2010-05-13}}</ref> and a pioneer in the field of [[History of the Jews in the United States|American Jewish history]].<ref>[http://magnes.org/collections/wjhc.html Western Jewish History Center || The Magnes<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060614001255/http://magnes.org/collections/wjhc.html |date=2006-06-14 }}</ref> Historian [[Selma Berrol]], however, has challenged the minimal treatment Rischin has given to the tensions between earlier German Jews and later Russian Jews in America.<ref>[http://www.historymatters.appstate.edu/documents/leofrank.pdf Jason Schulman<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070628225306/http://www.historymatters.appstate.edu/documents/leofrank.pdf |date=2007-06-28 }}</ref>
During the [[Monica Lewinsky scandal]], Rischin was a signatory of "Historians in Defense of the Constitution" wherein 400 historians criticized efforts to [[Impeachment of Bill Clinton|impeach President Bill Clinton]].<ref name="Salon">[http://www.salon.com/news/1998/10/30newslist.html Salon Newsreal | "Historians in Defense of the Constitution"<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref name="WP">{{cite news| url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-srv/politics/special/clinton/stories/petition102898.htm | work=The Washington Post | date=1998-10-30 | accessdate=2010-05-13}}</ref>
